{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846226954,"sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","part":{"id":"prt_d78aef805001BHw0jN8ysp70iJ","messageID":"msg_d78adb418001IqP9OYdcVNSCID","sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube вҖ” OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python вүҘ3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   вҶ’ Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      вҶ” Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      вҶ’ WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         вҶ” Redis/Valkey\n33:         вҶ’ K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube вҖ” OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python вүҘ3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775846226944,"end":1775846226952}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846226968,"sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","part":{"id":"prt_d78aef337001aOiknbFnWIoTPG","messageID":"msg_d78adb418001IqP9OYdcVNSCID","sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/common_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/common_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n21: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n22: )\n23: \n24: // Phase represents the common phase of a runtime resource.\n25: // This type is shared across different CRDs to provide consistent phase semantics.\n26: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n27: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n28: type Phase string\n29: \n30: const (\n31: \t// PhasePending indicates the resource is being created or initialized.\n32: \tPhasePending Phase = \"Pending\"\n33: \n34: \t// PhaseRunning indicates the resource is active and running.\n35: \tPhaseRunning Phase = \"Running\"\n36: \n37: \t// PhaseSucceeded indicates the resource completed successfully.\n38: \tPhaseSucceeded Phase = \"Succeeded\"\n39: \n40: \t// PhaseFailed indicates the resource has failed.\n41: \tPhaseFailed Phase = \"Failed\"\n42: \n43: \t// PhaseUnknown indicates the resource state is unknown.\n44: \tPhaseUnknown Phase = \"Unknown\"\n45: )\n46: \n47: // ConditionType represents a common condition type for runtime resources.\n48: // This type is shared across different CRDs to provide consistent condition semantics.\n49: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed;Scheduled;Initialized\n50: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n51: type ConditionType string\n52: \n53: const (\n54: \t// ConditionReady indicates the resource is ready to accept requests.\n55: \tConditionReady ConditionType = \"Ready\"\n56: \n57: \t// ConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n58: \tConditionSandboxCreated ConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n59: \n60: \t// ConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n61: \tConditionSandboxReady ConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n62: \n63: \t// ConditionFailed indicates the resource has failed.\n64: \tConditionFailed ConditionType = \"Failed\"\n65: \n66: \t// ConditionScheduled indicates the resource has been scheduled.\n67: \tConditionScheduled ConditionType = \"Scheduled\"\n68: \n69: \t// ConditionInitialized indicates the resource has been initialized.\n70: \tConditionInitialized ConditionType = \"Initialized\"\n71: )\n72: \n73: // Condition represents a common condition for runtime resources.\n74: // This struct is shared across different CRDs to provide consistent condition representation.\n75: type Condition struct {\n76: \t// Type is the type of the condition.\n77: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n78: \tType ConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n79: \n80: \t// Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n81: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n82: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n83: \tStatus corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n84: \n85: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n86: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n87: \tLastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n88: \n89: \t// Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n90: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n91: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n92: \n93: \t// Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n94: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n95: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n96: \n97: \t// ObservedGeneration is the observed generation of the resource.\n98: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n99: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n100: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n101: }\n102: \n103: // ResourceReference represents a reference to a Kubernetes resource.\n104: // This type is used to reference resources across different namespaces.\n105: type ResourceReference struct {\n106: \t// Name is the name of the referenced resource.\n107: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n108: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n109: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n110: \n111: \t// Namespace is the namespace of the referenced resource.\n112: \t// If not specified, the current namespace is used.\n113: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n114: \tNamespace string `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n115: }\n116: \n117: // LocalResourceReference represents a reference to a Kubernetes resource in the same namespace.\n118: type LocalResourceReference struct {\n119: \t// Name is the name of the referenced resource.\n120: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n121: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n122: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n123: }\n124: \n125: // SecretReference represents a reference to a Kubernetes Secret.\n126: type SecretReference struct {\n127: \t// Name is the name of the secret.\n128: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n129: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n130: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n131: \n132: \t// Key is the key within the secret to reference.\n133: \t// If not specified, all keys are referenced.\n134: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n135: \tKey string `json:\"key,omitempty\"`\n136: }\n137: \n138: // ConfigMapReference represents a reference to a Kubernetes ConfigMap.\n139: type ConfigMapReference struct {\n140: \t// Name is the name of the configmap.\n141: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n142: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n143: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n144: \n145: \t// Key is the key within the configmap to reference.\n146: \t// If not specified, all keys are referenced.\n147: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n148: \tKey string `json:\"key,omitempty\"`\n149: }\n150: \n151: // ResourceRequirements represents the compute resource requirements for a sandbox.\n152: // This is a wrapper around corev1.ResourceRequirements with additional validation.\n153: type ResourceRequirements struct {\n154: \t// Limits describes the maximum amount of compute resources allowed.\n155: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n156: \tLimits corev1.ResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n157: \n158: \t// Requests describes the minimum amount of compute resources required.\n159: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n160: \tRequests corev1.ResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n161: }\n162: \n163: // SandboxTemplate defines a common template for creating sandboxes.\n164: // This struct can be reused across different CRD types.\n165: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n166: \t// Labels are optional labels to apply to the sandbox pod.\n167: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n168: \t// +mapType=atomic\n169: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n170: \n171: \t// Annotations are optional annotations to apply to the sandbox pod.\n172: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n173: \t// +mapType=atomic\n174: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n175: \n176: \t// Spec is the Pod specification for the sandbox.\n177: \t// This field is optional and will be merged with default values.\n178: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n179: \tSpec *corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n180: }\n181: \n182: // StorageType represents the type of storage for volumes.\n183: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=EmptyDir;HostPath;PersistentVolumeClaim;ConfigMap;Secret\n184: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n185: type StorageType string\n186: \n187: const (\n188: \t// StorageTypeEmptyDir represents an empty directory storage.\n189: \tStorageTypeEmptyDir StorageType = \"EmptyDir\"\n190: \n191: \t// StorageTypeHostPath represents a host path storage.\n192: \tStorageTypeHostPath StorageType = \"HostPath\"\n193: \n194: \t// StorageTypePersistentVolumeClaim represents a PVC storage.\n195: \tStorageTypePersistentVolumeClaim StorageType = \"PersistentVolumeClaim\"\n196: \n197: \t// StorageTypeConfigMap represents a ConfigMap storage.\n198: \tStorageTypeConfigMap StorageType = \"ConfigMap\"\n199: \n200: \t// StorageTypeSecret represents a Secret storage.\n201: \tStorageTypeSecret StorageType = \"Secret\"\n202: )\n203: \n204: // VolumeSource represents a shared volume source definition.\n205: type VolumeSource struct {\n206: \t// Type is the type of storage.\n207: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n208: \tType StorageType `json:\"type\"`\n209: \n210: \t// EmptyDir represents an empty directory volume source.\n211: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n212: \tEmptyDir *corev1.EmptyDirVolumeSource `json:\"emptyDir,omitempty\"`\n213: \n214: \t// HostPath represents a host path volume source.\n215: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n216: \tHostPath *corev1.HostPathVolumeSource `json:\"hostPath,omitempty\"`\n217: \n218: \t// PersistentVolumeClaim represents a PVC volume source.\n219: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n220: \tPersistentVolumeClaim *corev1.PersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource `json:\"persistentVolumeClaim,omitempty\"`\n221: \n222: \t// ConfigMap represents a ConfigMap volume source.\n223: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n224: \tConfigMap *corev1.ConfigMapVolumeSource `json:\"configMap,omitempty\"`\n225: \n226: \t// Secret represents a Secret volume source.\n227: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n228: \tSecret *corev1.SecretVolumeSource `json:\"secret,omitempty\"`\n229: }\n230: \n231: // VolumeMount represents a mount point for a volume within a container.\n232: type VolumeMount struct {\n233: \t// Name is the name of the volume to mount.\n234: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n235: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n236: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n237: \n238: \t// MountPath is the path within the container where the volume should be mounted.\n239: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n240: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n241: \tMountPath string `json:\"mountPath\"`\n242: \n243: \t// ReadOnly indicates whether the mount should be read-only.\n244: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n245: \tReadOnly bool `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\"`\n246: \n247: \t// SubPath is the sub-path within the volume to mount.\n248: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n249: \tSubPath string `json:\"subPath,omitempty\"`\n250: }\n251: \n252: // NetworkConfig represents common network configuration for sandboxes.\n253: type NetworkConfig struct {\n254: \t// HostNetwork indicates whether to use the host's network namespace.\n255: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n256: \tHostNetwork bool `json:\"hostNetwork,omitempty\"`\n257: \n258: \t// HostPID indicates whether to use the host's PID namespace.\n259: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n260: \tHostPID bool `json:\"hostPID,omitempty\"`\n261: \n262: \t// HostIPC indicates whether to use the host's IPC namespace.\n263: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n264: \tHostIPC bool `json:\"hostIPC,omitempty\"`\n265: \n266: \t// DNSPolicy defines the DNS policy for the pod.\n267: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n268: \tDNSPolicy corev1.DNSPolicy `json:\"dnsPolicy,omitempty\"`\n269: \n270: \t// DNSConfig specifies the DNS parameters of the pod.\n271: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n272: \tDNSConfig *corev1.PodDNSConfig `json:\"dnsConfig,omitempty\"`\n273: }\n274: \n275: // SecurityContext represents common security context for sandboxes.\n276: type SecurityContext struct {\n277: \t// RunAsUser is the UID to run the entrypoint of the container process.\n278: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n279: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n280: \tRunAsUser *int64 `json:\"runAsUser,omitempty\"`\n281: \n282: \t// RunAsGroup is the GID to run the entrypoint of the container process.\n283: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n284: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n285: \tRunAsGroup *int64 `json:\"runAsGroup,omitempty\"`\n286: \n287: \t// RunAsNonRoot indicates that the container must run as a non-root user.\n288: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n289: \tRunAsNonRoot *bool `json:\"runAsNonRoot,omitempty\"`\n290: \n291: \t// ReadOnlyRootFilesystem indicates whether the container's root filesystem is read-only.\n292: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n293: \tReadOnlyRootFilesystem *bool `json:\"readOnlyRootFilesystem,omitempty\"`\n294: \n295: \t// Privileged indicates whether the container is privileged.\n296: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n297: \tPrivileged *bool `json:\"privileged,omitempty\"`\n298: \n299: \t// AllowPrivilegeEscalation controls whether a process can gain more privileges than its parent process.\n300: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n301: \tAllowPrivilegeEscalation *bool `json:\"allowPrivilegeEscalation,omitempty\"`\n302: }\n303: \n304: // LifecycleHooks represents lifecycle hooks for sandbox containers.\n305: type LifecycleHooks struct {\n306: \t// PostStart is a hook that is called after the container is started.\n307: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n308: \tPostStart *corev1.LifecycleHandler `json:\"postStart,omitempty\"`\n309: \n310: \t// PreStop is a hook that is called before the container is terminated.\n311: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n312: \tPreStop *corev1.LifecycleHandler `json:\"preStop,omitempty\"`\n313: }\n314: \n315: // HealthCheck represents health check configuration for sandboxes.\n316: type HealthCheck struct {\n317: \t// LivenessProbe specifies the liveness probe configuration.\n318: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n319: \tLivenessProbe *corev1.Probe `json:\"livenessProbe,omitempty\"`\n320: \n321: \t// ReadinessProbe specifies the readiness probe configuration.\n322: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n323: \tReadinessProbe *corev1.Probe `json:\"readinessProbe,omitempty\"`\n324: \n325: \t// StartupProbe specifies the startup probe configuration.\n326: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n327: \tStartupProbe *corev1.Probe `json:\"startupProbe,omitempty\"`\n328: }\n329: \n330: // TimeoutConfig represents timeout configuration for sandbox resources.\n331: type TimeoutConfig struct {\n332: \t// TTLSecondsAfterFinished specifies the time to live (in seconds) after\n333: \t// the resource has finished (succeeded or failed).\n334: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n335: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n336: \tTTLSecondsAfterFinished *int32 `json:\"ttlSecondsAfterFinished,omitempty\"`\n337: \n338: \t// IdleTimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum time (in seconds) the resource\n339: \t// can be idle before being terminated.\n340: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n341: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n342: \tIdleTimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"idleTimeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n343: \n344: \t// MaxLifetimeSeconds specifies the maximum lifetime (in seconds) of the resource.\n345: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n346: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n347: \tMaxLifetimeSeconds *int32 `json:\"maxLifetimeSeconds,omitempty\"`\n348: \n349: \t// GracePeriodSeconds specifies the duration in seconds the pod needs to\n350: \t// terminate gracefully upon deletion.\n351: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n352: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n353: \tGracePeriodSeconds *int64 `json:\"gracePeriodSeconds,omitempty\"`\n354: }\n\n(End of file - total 354 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/common_types.go","time":{"start":1775846226941,"end":1775846226965}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775846226997,"sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","part":{"id":"prt_d78aefc18001vD7Q6ppMpteV7k","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78adb418001IqP9OYdcVNSCID","sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":51266,"input":4,"output":151,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":9165,"read":41946}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775846272477,"sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","part":{"id":"prt_d78afadda001szw2IYKFN20LNH","messageID":"msg_d78aefc4d001yCqjUMMFMBOto9","sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775846274011,"sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","part":{"id":"prt_d78afb24e001zxtlx2G4U6C81a","messageID":"msg_d78aefc4d001yCqjUMMFMBOto9","sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context. Let me create the delta-spec.md for AR-005:","time":{"start":1775846274008,"end":1775846274008}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775846400391,"sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","part":{"id":"prt_d78b08580001ezp5xP0iFhrhF2","messageID":"msg_d78aefc4d001yCqjUMMFMBOto9","sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","type":"text","text":" the","time":{"start":1775846400388,"end":1775846400388}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846400414,"sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","part":{"id":"prt_d78afb3da001eWuIw3V6rx35Ag","messageID":"msg_d78aefc4d001yCqjUMMFMBOto9","sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 вҖ” Sandbox еҲӣе»әеӨ„зҗҶеҷЁ\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-005  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the Sandbox creation handler for the WorkloadManager that processes sandbox creation requests from `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, provisions isolated execution environments for agents, and manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources. The handler integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and the generated client-go library (AR-003).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from AgentRuntime workload definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-runtime` exists in namespace `default` with a valid pod template\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"test-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL:\n  1. Validate the request (Kind=AgentRuntime, name and namespace non-empty)\n  2. Retrieve the AgentRuntime from informer cache\n  3. Build a Sandbox object with generated name `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n  4. Create placeholder in Store with status \"pending\"\n  5. Register watcher before creating CR to avoid race conditions\n  6. Create the Sandbox CR via dynamic client\n  7. Wait up to 2 minutes for Sandbox to reach \"running\" status\n  8. Resolve Pod IP and build entryPoints from spec.Ports\n  9. Update Store with full SandboxInfo including entryPoints\n  10. Return HTTP 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing sessionId and entryPoints\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing pod template\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `invalid-runtime` exists in namespace `default` with `spec.template=nil`\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"invalid-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message containing \"pod template\"\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox for non-existent AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `missing-runtime` exists in namespace `default`\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"missing-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"agent runtime not found\"\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox with invalid request body\n- **GIVEN** a malformed JSON payload\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with invalid JSON\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"Invalid request body\"\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing required fields\n- **GIVEN** a request missing the `name` field\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"name is required\"\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing namespace\n- **GIVEN** a request missing the `namespace` field\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"test-runtime\"}`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"namespace is required\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from CodeInterpreter workload definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid CodeInterpreter\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter` exists in namespace `default` with valid template\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{\"name\": \"test-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL:\n  1. Validate the request (Kind=CodeInterpreter, name and namespace non-empty)\n  2. Retrieve the CodeInterpreter from informer cache\n  3. Build a Sandbox or SandboxClaim object based on WarmPoolSize\n  4. Apply default ports `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if spec.Ports is empty\n  5. Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var if AuthMode=picod and publicKey is available\n  6. Follow the same creation and wait flow as AgentRuntime\n  7. Return HTTP 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse`\n\n#### Scenario: Create SandboxClaim for warm pool\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `warm-interpreter` exists with `WarmPoolSize > 0`\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL create a `SandboxClaim` (not full Sandbox) with Kind=\"SandboxClaim\"\n\n#### Scenario: Create full Sandbox for non-warm pool\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `cold-interpreter` exists with `WarmPoolSize=0` or unset\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL create a full `Sandbox` with single container named `code-interpreter`\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox for non-existent CodeInterpreter\n- **GIVEN** no CodeInterpreter named `missing-interpreter` exists\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{\"name\": \"missing-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"code interpreter not found\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox Object Building\n\nThe system SHALL build proper Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Build Sandbox object with correct metadata\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with name `my-runtime` and a sessionID `sess-123`\n- **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n- **THEN** the resulting Sandbox SHALL have:\n  - Name: `my-runtime-{8-char-random}`\n  - APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n  - Kind: `Sandbox`\n  - Labels:\n    - `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`: sessionID\n    - `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`: runtime.Name\n    - `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name`: sandboxName\n    - `managed-by`: `agentcube-workload-manager`\n  - Annotations:\n    - `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`: SessionTimeout (default \"15m\")\n\n#### Scenario: Build Sandbox with lifecycle settings\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration` set to 8 hours\n- **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n- **THEN** the Sandbox spec SHALL include `lifecycle.shutdownTime` set to `now + MaxSessionDuration`\n\n#### Scenario: Build CodeInterpreter Sandbox with auth mode\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `AuthMode=picod` and a public key available\n- **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n- **THEN** the container SHALL have environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` set to the public key\n\n#### Scenario: Build CodeInterpreter Sandbox without auth\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `AuthMode=none`\n- **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n- **THEN** the container SHALL NOT have `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: Build SandboxClaim for warm pool\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize=5`\n- **WHEN** `buildSandboxClaimObject()` is called\n- **THEN** the resulting object SHALL have:\n  - APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n  - Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n  - Minimal metadata (no full PodSpec)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox Creation and Wait Flow\n\nThe system SHALL orchestrate the creation flow with proper synchronization and timeouts.\n\n#### Scenario: Register watcher before CR creation\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox object ready to be created\n- **WHEN** `createSandbox()` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `WatchSandboxOnce()` to register the watcher BEFORE calling `dynamicClient.Create()`\n\n#### Scenario: Store placeholder before CR creation\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox object ready to be created\n- **WHEN** `createSandbox()` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `StoreSandbox()` with status \"pending\" BEFORE creating the CR\n\n#### Scenario: Successfully wait for sandbox running\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR has been created\n- **WHEN** the SandboxReconciler notifies the sandbox is running within 2 minutes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Receive notification from the watcher channel\n  2. Resolve Pod IP using `resolvePodIP()`\n  3. Build entryPoints from ports and Pod IP\n  4. Update Store with status \"running\" and entryPoints\n  5. Return the complete SandboxInfo\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout waiting for sandbox running\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR has been created but does not reach running state\n- **WHEN** 2 minutes elapse without receiving running notification\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Cancel the wait context\n  2. Delete the CR with a 30-second timeout context\n  3. Delete the Store placeholder\n  4. Return error \"sandbox creation timed out\"\n\n#### Scenario: Pod IP resolution from annotation\n- **GIVEN** a running Sandbox with annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name=my-pod`\n- **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL first check the annotation and use `my-pod` as the pod name to look up\n\n#### Scenario: Pod IP resolution from owner reference\n- **GIVEN** a running Sandbox without pod name annotation\n- **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name` and select the one with OwnerReference matching the Sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: Pod IP resolution failure\n- **GIVEN** no running pod exists for the sandbox\n- **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return error \"no running pod found for sandbox {name}\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Rollback and Cleanup\n\nThe system SHALL implement proper rollback on creation failures.\n\n#### Scenario: Rollback on CR creation failure\n- **GIVEN** Store placeholder has been created\n- **WHEN** dynamic client Create() fails\n- **THEN** the system SHALL delete the Store placeholder using `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()`\n\n#### Scenario: Rollback on timeout\n- **GIVEN** CR has been created but sandbox never reaches running\n- **WHEN** timeout occurs after 2 minutes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Delete the CR using dynamic client with 30s timeout\n  2. Delete the Store placeholder\n  3. Return timeout error\n\n#### Scenario: Rollback on Pod IP resolution failure\n- **GIVEN** CR has been created and sandbox is running\n- **WHEN** Pod IP resolution fails\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Delete the CR\n  2. Delete the Store placeholder\n  3. Return resolution error\n\n#### Scenario: Handle Store update failure\n- **GIVEN** CR is created and running, Pod IP is resolved\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox()` fails\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Log warning about Store inconsistency\n  2. CR will be eventually cleaned up by GC\n  3. Return the error\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Request Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate CreateSandboxRequest according to defined rules.\n\n#### Scenario: Validate valid request\n- **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with `Kind=\"AgentRuntime\"`, `Name=\"test\"`, `Namespace=\"default\"`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return nil (no error)\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects empty name\n- **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with empty `Name` field\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"name is required\"\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects empty namespace\n- **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with empty `Namespace` field\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"namespace is required\"\n\n#### Scenario: Validate rejects invalid kind\n- **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with `Kind=\"InvalidKind\"`\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"kind is required\" (or invalid kind)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Response Building\n\nThe system SHALL build proper CreateSandboxResponse from SandboxInfo.\n\n#### Scenario: Build response with entryPoints\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with:\n  - SessionID: `sess-abc-123`\n  - SandboxID: `runtime-xyz-789`\n  - SandboxName: `my-runtime-abcdef12`\n  - EntryPoints: `[{Path: \"/\", Protocol: \"HTTP\", Endpoint: \"10.244.0.5:8080\"}]`\n- **WHEN** building the HTTP response\n- **THEN** the response SHALL contain:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"sessionId\": \"sess-abc-123\",\n    \"sandboxId\": \"runtime-xyz-789\",\n    \"sandboxName\": \"my-runtime-abcdef12\",\n    \"entryPoints\": [\n      {\n        \"path\": \"/\",\n        \"protocol\": \"HTTP\",\n        \"endpoint\": \"10.244.0.5:8080\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Authentication Integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with authentication middleware when enabled.\n\n#### Scenario: Extract auth context when auth enabled\n- **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has valid Authorization header\n- **WHEN** the handler processes the request\n- **THEN** the context SHALL contain:\n  - `contextKeyUserToken`: the bearer token\n  - `contextKeyServiceAccount`: the service account name\n  - `contextKeyNamespace`: the namespace for per-user client caching\n\n#### Scenario: Reject request without auth header\n- **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has no Authorization header\n- **WHEN** authMiddleware processes the request\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with message \"Missing authorization header\"\n\n#### Scenario: Reject invalid token\n- **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has invalid token\n- **WHEN** authMiddleware calls TokenReview\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with TokenReview error message\n\n#### Scenario: Use per-user client when auth enabled\n- **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and auth context is present\n- **WHEN** creating the Sandbox CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()` to get per-user dynamic client\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Idempotency\n\nThe system SHALL support idempotent creation requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Return existing session for duplicate request\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox creation request for AgentRuntime `test-runtime` has already succeeded with sessionID `sess-123`\n- **WHEN** the same request is made again\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Check Store for existing session by workload name\n  2. Return the existing sessionID without creating new sandbox\n  3. Return HTTP 200 with original CreateSandboxResponse\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling and HTTP Status Mapping\n\nThe system SHALL map internal errors to appropriate HTTP status codes.\n\n#### Scenario: Map JSON binding error to 400\n- **GIVEN** request body is malformed JSON\n- **WHEN** `c.ShouldBindJSON()` fails\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"Invalid request body\"\n\n#### Scenario: Map validation error to 400\n- **GIVEN** request fails validation (missing required field)\n- **WHEN** `Validate()` returns error\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with validation error message\n\n#### Scenario: Map not found to 404\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is not found in informer cache\n- **WHEN** lookup fails\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with appropriate \"not found\" message\n\n#### Scenario: Map internal errors to 500\n- **GIVEN** an unexpected internal error occurs (Store failure, K8s API error)\n- **WHEN** error is processed\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 500 with message \"internal server error\" (details logged but not exposed)\n\n#### Scenario: Map timeout to 500\n- **GIVEN** sandbox creation times out after 2 minutes\n- **WHEN** timeout occurs\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 500 with message \"internal server error\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Context Propagation\n\nThe system SHALL properly propagate context through the creation flow.\n\n#### Scenario: Pass context through creation flow\n- **GIVEN** a request context with requestID and auth info\n- **WHEN** the creation flow executes (validate вҶ’ build вҶ’ create вҶ’ wait)\n- **THEN** the context SHALL be passed to all operations for cancellation and timeout handling\n\n#### Scenario: Handle context cancellation during wait\n- **GIVEN** sandbox is waiting for running status\n- **WHEN** the parent context is cancelled (e.g., client disconnects)\n- **THEN** the wait SHALL be cancelled and resources cleaned up\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Timeout Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL enforce configurable timeouts for sandbox operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Enforce 2-minute creation timeout\n- **GIVEN** default timeout configuration\n- **WHEN** creating sandbox with `context.WithTimeout(ctx, 2*time.Minute)`\n- **THEN** the operation SHALL timeout after 2 minutes if sandbox doesn't reach running\n\n#### Scenario: Enforce 30-second deletion timeout on rollback\n- **GIVEN** rollback is triggered after creation timeout\n- **WHEN** deleting the CR\n- **THEN** the deletion SHALL use `context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)`\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | `sandboxCreator` struct and `createSandbox()` orchestration |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | `buildSandboxObject()`, `buildSandboxClaimObject()`, `resolvePodIP()`, `buildEntryPoints()` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | `SandboxReconciler`, `WatchSandboxOnce()`, sandbox status tracking |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | GVR definitions, `Informers` struct, informer lifecycle |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | `K8sClient`, `ClientCache`, `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go` | `authMiddleware`, context keys, token validation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`, label/annotation keys |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox.go` | Sandbox domain types (if not in pkg/apis) |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go` | Handler unit tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` | Sandbox creation flow tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` | Object building tests |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated Kubernetes clientset, informers, listers |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Dynamic client, REST client |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery, unstructured |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Latest | HTTP framework (inherited from AR-004) |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | Latest | UUID generation for sessionID |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | Latest | Test dependency for mock Redis |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | Create sandbox from AgentRuntime definition |\n| POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | Create sandbox from CodeInterpreter definition |\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n### CreateSandboxRequest\n```go\ntype CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n    Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`      // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`      // workload name\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"` // workload namespace\n}\n```\n\n### CreateSandboxResponse\n```go\ntype CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n    SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`     // route path prefix\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"` // \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"` // \"host:port\"\n}\n```\n\n### SandboxInfo (Store model)\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string                `json:\"kind\"`             // \"Sandbox\" or \"SandboxClaim\"\n    SandboxID        string                `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace string                `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    Name             string                `json:\"name\"`\n    SessionID        string                `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint   `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    Status           string                `json:\"status\"`           // \"pending\", \"running\", \"failed\"\n    CreatedAt        time.Time             `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time             `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration with client-go\n\n| Component | Usage |\n|-----------|-------|\n| `clientset/versioned.Interface` | Get typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n| `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` | Informer lifecycle management |\n| `listers/runtime/v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister` | Read-only AgentRuntime queries |\n| `listers/runtime/v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister` | Read-only CodeInterpreter queries |\n| `fake.Clientset` | Unit test mocks |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- Watcher MUST be registered BEFORE creating the CR to avoid race conditions where Sandbox enters running before watcher is ready\n- Store placeholder MUST be created BEFORE CR creation for idempotency and rollback\n- Dynamic client is used for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs (external to agentcube)\n- Per-user K8s client is used when authentication is enabled\n- All timeouts are configurable via constants in `defaults.go`\n- EntryPoints are built from `spec.Ports` with format: `{PathPrefix, Protocol, PodIP:Port}`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\">\nERROR [22:2] error while importing k8s.io/api/core/v1: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/net/http2 (imported by k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net); to add:\n\tgo get k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net@v0.32.0\nERROR [23:2] error while importing k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/net/http2 (imported by k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net); to add:\n\tgo get k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net@v0.32.0\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod\">\nERROR [11:2] error while importing k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/net/http2 (imported by k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net); to add:\n\tgo get k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net@v0.32.0\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go\">\nERROR [20:2] error while importing k8s.io/api/core/v1: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/net/http2 (imported by k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net); to add:\n\tgo get k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net@v0.32.0\nERROR [21:2] error while importing k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/net/http2 (imported by k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net); to add:\n\tgo get k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/net@v0.32.0\n</diagnostics