{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846432227,"sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","part":{"id":"prt_d78b21530001lVlgC2K8lPMn5G","messageID":"msg_d78b1a1d3001vKIG8by2JwJJp4","sessionID":"ses_28752f7a2ffeaJZJbHq9rT1whF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 вҖ” Sandbox еҲӣе»әеӨ„зҗҶеҷЁ\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-005  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Implement the Sandbox creation handler for the WorkloadManager that processes sandbox creation requests from `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, provisions isolated execution environments for agents, and manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources. The handler integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and the generated client-go library (AR-003).\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n17: \n18: The system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from AgentRuntime workload definitions.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid AgentRuntime\n21: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-runtime` exists in namespace `default` with a valid pod template\n22: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"test-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n23: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n24:   1. Validate the request (Kind=AgentRuntime, name and namespace non-empty)\n25:   2. Retrieve the AgentRuntime from informer cache\n26:   3. Build a Sandbox object with generated name `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n27:   4. Create placeholder in Store with status \"pending\"\n28:   5. Register watcher before creating CR to avoid race conditions\n29:   6. Create the Sandbox CR via dynamic client\n30:   7. Wait up to 2 minutes for Sandbox to reach \"running\" status\n31:   8. Resolve Pod IP and build entryPoints from spec.Ports\n32:   9. Update Store with full SandboxInfo including entryPoints\n33:   10. Return HTTP 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing sessionId and entryPoints\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing pod template\n36: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `invalid-runtime` exists in namespace `default` with `spec.template=nil`\n37: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"invalid-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message containing \"pod template\"\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Create sandbox for non-existent AgentRuntime\n41: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `missing-runtime` exists in namespace `default`\n42: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"missing-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n43: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"agent runtime not found\"\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with invalid request body\n46: - **GIVEN** a malformed JSON payload\n47: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with invalid JSON\n48: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"Invalid request body\"\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing required fields\n51: - **GIVEN** a request missing the `name` field\n52: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n53: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"name is required\"\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing namespace\n56: - **GIVEN** a request missing the `namespace` field\n57: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"test-runtime\"}`\n58: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"namespace is required\"\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n63: \n64: The system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from CodeInterpreter workload definitions.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid CodeInterpreter\n67: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter` exists in namespace `default` with valid template\n68: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{\"name\": \"test-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n69: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n70:   1. Validate the request (Kind=CodeInterpreter, name and namespace non-empty)\n71:   2. Retrieve the CodeInterpreter from informer cache\n72:   3. Build a Sandbox or SandboxClaim object based on WarmPoolSize\n73:   4. Apply default ports `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if spec.Ports is empty\n74:   5. Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var if AuthMode=picod and publicKey is available\n75:   6. Follow the same creation and wait flow as AgentRuntime\n76:   7. Return HTTP 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse`\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Create SandboxClaim for warm pool\n79: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `warm-interpreter` exists with `WarmPoolSize > 0`\n80: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n81: - **THEN** the server SHALL create a `SandboxClaim` (not full Sandbox) with Kind=\"SandboxClaim\"\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Create full Sandbox for non-warm pool\n84: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `cold-interpreter` exists with `WarmPoolSize=0` or unset\n85: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n86: - **THEN** the server SHALL create a full `Sandbox` with single container named `code-interpreter`\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Create sandbox for non-existent CodeInterpreter\n89: - **GIVEN** no CodeInterpreter named `missing-interpreter` exists\n90: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{\"name\": \"missing-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n91: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"code interpreter not found\"\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: Sandbox Object Building\n96: \n97: The system SHALL build proper Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload definitions.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Build Sandbox object with correct metadata\n100: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with name `my-runtime` and a sessionID `sess-123`\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 489. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 вҖ” Sandbox еҲӣе»әеӨ„зҗҶеҷЁ\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-005  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the Sandbox creation handler for the WorkloadManager that processes sandbox creation requests from `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, provisions isolated execution environments for agents, and manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources. The handler integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and the generated client-go library (AR-003).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from AgentRuntime workload definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid AgentRuntime","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775846432215,"end":1775846432225}}}}
